<a name="HowToCook"></a>
<b>How to Cook</b>
<ul>
<li>Poultry must be cooked to 160-165 degrees to kill salmonella</li>
<li>When meat is cooked to at least 160 degrees, any and all[harmful] bacteria will be killed Not things like BSE or rancidity</li>
<li>For rare meat, cooking temperature should be 120-130 degrees to 140</li>
<li>The internal temperature of meat will rise 5-10 degrees after it is removed from the heat</li>
<li>The thicker the meat, the higher the internal temperature will continue to rise be upon removing from heat</li>
<li>Fresh Direct Polish Kielbasa:<br>Can be pan fried or baked in the oven.<br>If baked put in a pan with a little water and bake at about 375 F until sausage is about 170 F internal.</li>
</ul>
