<a name="FreshnessFreezing"></a>
<b>Freshness/Freezing</b>
<ul>
<li>If meat is kept refrigerated (38 degrees)[34-36 is  better but 38 will not compromise] and is used/frozen by the date on the package, the product's integrity will not be compromised</li>
<li>Standard packaging is not ideal for freezing - we do not recommend freezing meat for longer than 3 weeks without Vacuum Packaging </li>
<li>Freezing meat in improper packaging will result in crystallizing [dehydration] if it frozen for more than 3 weeks</li>
<li>Even with Vacuum Packaging, we do not recommend freezing meat for longer than 6 months</li>
<li>We recommend that meat which was frozen must be used immediately once defrosted</li>
<li>Freezing meat causes ice crystals which a break down  the cells that will cause more liquid to escape - you will lose flavor & consistency if this happens </li>
<li>"Blast Freezing" avoids cell breakdown because the meat will freeze at a much faster rate - ice crystals will be smaller, if at all</li>
<li>Never defrost meat products at room temperature - this is the perfect temperature for bacteria to grow - always defrost meat in the refrigerator or Running water or microwave</li>
<li>Marinades can be frozen with the meat - they are packaged separately[Push vacuum plus which packages it separately]</li>
</ul>
